# ProjectFlo — Backend Architecture

- New backend feature code must live under exactly one bucket: `platform`, `catalog`, `workflow`, `content`, or `finance`. Do not create new top-level buckets under `packages/backend/src`.
- Treat `src/platform/logging/logger.service.ts`, `src/platform/logging/request-logger.middleware.ts`, `src/platform/prisma/prisma.service.ts`, and `src/platform/auth/` as protected infrastructure — never delete, move, or rename them without explicit user direction.
- Use precise file naming: `feature.module.ts`, `feature.controller.ts`, `feature.service.ts`, `feature.mapper.ts`, `create-feature.dto.ts`, `update-feature.dto.ts`, etc. Avoid vague files like `utils.ts`, `helpers.ts`, or `common.ts`.
- Keep services focused on a single responsibility; split CRUD, relationship management, mapping, and admin logic into separate services or mappers when they grow.
- Respect size limits: services ≈250 lines, controllers ≈200, DTOs ≈120, methods target 40 lines (60 hard max); refactor before adding new logic to oversized files.
- Avoid `any` in services, controllers, and mappers; use Prisma payload types, DTOs, or explicit local types instead.
- Every backend module folder should have a `README.md`; read it before editing and update it when changing business rules, key files, or cross-references.

